divs: sighting detailsi was outside smoking when i noticed a star like object in the sky to the west-southwest about 5 miles from my location putting it almost over the city of dublin. it was a cloudy night & the moon was very bright there where no stars visible & this object was fairly close to me & the ground. it flashed a few times moved back & forth stopped & just sat for awhile before repeating it's earlier activity. then it slowly moved away directly to the west. towards the comanche county\lake proctor area. the whole incident was about 20 minutes long & had noticed similiar object(s) in the sky earlier in the evening just before sundown except that object from earlier that evening did all the smae movements but it slowly dropped to the ground & dissapeared from my view to the northwest.
